triageapp.components

Class Patient

  • java.lang.Object
    • triageapp.components.Patient
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class Patient
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Class Patient holds the patient's personal information and medical history. It is used to access and update the Patient's medical record, and keep track of the patient's current ER visit.
    See Also:

    • Constructor Detail

      • Patient

        public Patient(String name,
       String dob,
       String healthCardNumber)
        throws InvalidUserInputException
        Constructs a Patient using their name, date of birth, and healthcard number. Their urgency points is initially set to 0, their medicalRecord does not exist, and they do not have an ERVisit.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the Patient.
        dob - The date of birth of the patient, expressed as a String.
        healthCardNumber - The health card number of the Patient.
        Throws:
        InvalidUserInputException
